## RuneTreeManager.fetchRune() method

Fetch a rune by its key. The key is mostly the same as the rune name, for example - `Electrocute`<!-- -->.

<b>Signature:</b>

```typescript
fetchRune(key: string, options?: {
        force: boolean;
    }): Promise<Rune>;
```

## Parameters

|  Parameter | Type | Description |
|  --- | --- | --- |
|  key | string | The key of the rune. |
|  options | { force: boolean; } | <i>(Optional)</i> Additional fetch options. |

Promise&lt;[Rune](./shieldbow.rune.md)<!-- -->&gt;
